### BUG-009-V2 [P0] AbortError still firing — root cause is in useInvoices.ts
Files: src/hooks/useInvoices.ts, src/hooks/useClients.ts

CONFIRMED by reading source code:
useJobs.ts is correctly fixed.
useClients.ts is correctly fixed.

The AbortError is coming from useInvoices.ts — specifically the
useInvoicesByContractor hook which is called inside the Sidebar
component via useOverdueCount(). This runs on EVERY page because
the sidebar mounts on every authenticated route.

The problem is in useInvoice and useInvoiceByToken — both still have
t() in their useCallback dependency arrays:

  // useInvoice — BROKEN
  const queryFn = useCallback(async () => {
    if (!id) {
      throw { message: t('validation.invoiceIdRequired'), ... }
    }
    ...
  }, [id, t]);  // <-- t causes recreation every render

  // useInvoiceByToken — BROKEN
  const queryFn = useCallback(async () => {
    if (!token) {
      throw { message: t('validation.invoiceTokenRequired'), ... }
    }
    ...
  }, [token, t]);  // <-- t causes recreation every render

FIX for useInvoice:
  Extract the validation message outside the callback using a ref
  or move the t() call outside useCallback entirely:

  const { t } = useTranslation();
  const tRef = useRef(t);
  useEffect(() => { tRef.current = t; }, [t]);

  const queryFn = useCallback(async ({ signal }: { signal?: AbortSignal }) => {
    if (!id) {
      throw { message: tRef.current('validation.invoiceIdRequired'), reason: 'validation' } satisfies RepositoryError;
    }
    const result = await invoiceRepository.get(id, signal);
    if (result.error || !result.data) {
      throw result.error ?? { message: 'Unknown error', reason: 'unknown' };
    }
    return result.data;
  }, [id]);  // t removed — use tRef.current instead

FIX for useInvoiceByToken — same pattern:
  Use tRef.current inside callback instead of t directly.
  Remove t from dependency array.
  Add signal parameter to queryFn.

ALSO CHECK: useInvoicesByContractor in the same file is used by the
Sidebar on every page. Confirm it uses TanStack native signal and has
no t() dependency. Looking at the source it appears correct — but
verify it does not trigger the abort by adding a console.log temporarily
to confirm it resolves successfully when the sidebar mounts.

Commit: fix(BUG-009-V2): remove t() from useInvoice and useInvoiceByToken queryFn deps

