### BUG-017 [P1] Settings profile fields empty on load
File: src/pages/SettingsPage.tsx (find actual path)

The profile fields (First Name, Last Name, Business Name, Phone)
are all blank on load. The profile data IS in the DB. The form is
not being initialized with values from useAuth().profile.

Find the settings form and ensure it uses useEffect or defaultValues
to seed form fields from profile when profile becomes available:

  const { profile } = useAuth();
  const { register, reset } = useForm();

  useEffect(() => {
    if (profile) {
      const nameParts = profile.full_name?.split(' ') ?? [];
      reset({
        firstName: nameParts[0] ?? '',
        lastName: nameParts.slice(1).join(' ') ?? '',
        businessName: profile.business_name ?? '',
        phone: profile.phone ?? '',
      });
    }
  }, [profile, reset]);

Also: the "Unable to update profile." error should only show AFTER
a failed save attempt, not on page load. Find the error state and
wrap it with a condition: only show if formState.isSubmitted or
a save was attempted.

